  <title>Gio.FILE_ATTRIBUTE_STANDARD_ALLOCATED_SIZE</title>
  <p>A key in the "standard" namespace for getting the amount of disk space
that is consumed by the file (in bytes).  This will generally be larger
than the file size (due to block size overhead) but can occasionally be
smaller (for example, for sparse files).
Corresponding <link xref="Gio.FileAttributeType"/> is <link xref="Gio.FileAttributeType"/>.uint64.</p>
  <p>Since 2.20</p>
